Body
(
Fig. 5A
) 7.3 times longer than wide, brow, covered with scales and some tiny setae. Cephalon almost as long as wide, 0.7 times the length of pereonite 1, rostrum slightly larger than lateral angles; eyes with approximately 14 omatids. Pleon (
Fig. 5B
) 1.1 times longer than telson, with suture lines between each pleonite. Uropods subequal in length to telson; 
telson
(
Fig. 5C
) 2.2 times longer than broad and 0.9 times the length of pleon, distal margin with 16 setae.
